ng%20the%20decline%20of%20Electric%20Vehicles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580a0d61c5c7b8c9a0960bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFewer%20people%20are%20buying%20electric%20cars%20%E2%80%94%20the%20slowdown%20hints%20at%20a%20problem%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20America's%20EV%20push.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EElectric%20vehicles%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20inevitable.%20Two%20years%20ago%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20climbed%20behind%20the%20wheel%20of%20a%20beefy%20white%20electric%20Hummer%20to%20tout%20his%20plan%20to%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-executive-order-electric-cars-evs-2030-target-half-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehalf%20of%20all%20new%20cars%20sold%20electric%20by%202030%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20following%20year%20Congress%20passed%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%2C%20which%20created%20a%20bevy%20of%20incentives%20for%20drivers%20to%20buy%20electric%20and%20for%20automakers%20to%20invest%20in%20EVs.%20That%20set%20off%20a%20flurry%20of%20new%20projects%3A%20EV%20plants%2C%20battery-manufacturing%20facilities%2C%20and%20mining%20operations%20began%20popping%20up.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202022%20the%20situation%20looked%20promising%3A%20More%20and%20more%20Americans%20were%20going%20electric%2C%20and%20soon%20everyone%20would%20be%20driving%20an%20EV%2C%20reducing%20emissions%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20transition%20to%20an%20all-EV%20future%20seemed%20like%20a%20slam%20dunk.%20It%20would%20not%20only%20give%20the%20government%20a%20highly%20visible%20way%20to%20show%20it's%20fighting%20the%20climate%20crisis%20but%20boost%20the%20economy%20through%20new%20jobs%20and%20investment.%20But%20the%20electric-vehicle%20takeover%20has%20hit%20some%20serious%20roadblocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%