lanned%20factory%20in%20Mexico.%20Auto%20execs%20who%20were%20once%20trumpeting%20the%20potential%20of%20electric%20cars%20are%20even%20publicly%20acknowledging%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauto-executives-coming-clean-evs-arent-working-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEVs%20aren't%20working%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20analysts%20have%20pointed%20to%20several%20reasons%20for%20the%20slowdown%2C%20including%20insufficient%20charging%20infrastructure%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20affordable%20EV%20options.%20But%20they're%20a%20symptom%20of%20the%20larger%20problem%3A%20America's%20EV%20plan%20was%20flawed%20from%20the%20start.%20Instead%20of%20seeing%20EVs%20as%20one%20piece%20of%20a%20plan%20for%20more%20sustainable%20transportation%2C%20America%20has%20focused%20on%20using%20EVs%20as%20a%20one-to-one%20replacement%20for%20gas%20guzzlers.%20But%20this%20one-size-fits-all%20solution%20fails%20to%20address%20our%20broader%20transportation%20problems%2C%20meaning%20emissions%20targets%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20missed%20and%20other%20transportation%20problems%20will%20continue%20to%20go%20unaddressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20entire%20myth%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20whole%20transition%20is%20that%20the%20battery%20car%20seamlessly%20fits%20right%20into%20the%20gas%20car's%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20Edward%20Niedermeyer%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BLudicrous%3A%20The%20Unvarnished%20Story%20of%20Tesla%20Motors%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%2C%20and%20that's%20the%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20EV%20myth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20to%20replace%20gas%20cars%20with%20EVs%20has%20led%20to%20a%20series%20of%20major%20miscalculations%2C%20one%20of%20which%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20sheer%20size%20of%20the%20new%20electric%20vehicles%20being%20put%20on%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20decades%20the%20American%20auto%20industry%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froad-rage-speeding-driving-traffic-large-expensive-cars-suv-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebecome%20obsessed%20with%20huge%20vehicles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20reasons%20for%20the%20size%20inflation%20range%20from%20profit%20margins%20to%20distorted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fnews%2Fsmall-cars-are-getting-huge-are-fuel-economy-regulations-to-blame%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egovernment%20fuel%20standards%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20proliferation%20of%20bigger%20vehicles%20created%20a%20doom%20loop%20of%20consumer%20preference%3A%20Drivers%20saw%20the%20vehicles%20around%20them%20getting%20bigger%2C%20so%20they%20wanted%20bigger%20cars%20to%20make%20themselves%20feel%20safer.%20Automakers%20argued%20that%20this%20was%20proof%20that%20people%20wanted%20only%20big%20cars%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-small-car-market-is-a-disaster-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethey%20cut%20small%20models%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20made%20existing%20vehicles%20bigger%2C%20which%20made%20people%20with%20smaller%20cars%20feel%20less%20safe%20%E2%80%94%20you%20get%20the%20picture.%20Meanwhile%2C%20road%20deaths%20and%20injuries%20soared%2C%20while%20the%20larger%2C%20less%20efficient%20vehicles%20wiped%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F07%2F28%2F1190799503%2Fnew-fuel-economy-standards-cars-trucks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenvironmental%20benefits%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20higher%20emissions%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20automakers%20pivoted%20to%20EVs%2C%20they%20focused%20on%20the%20kinds%20of%20cars%20that%20were%20already%20popular%20%E2%80%94%20which%20meant%20a%20flood%20of%20big%20electrified%20SUVs%20and%20trucks.%20But%20massive-bodied%20EVs%20don't%20make%20much%20sense.%20Larger%20EVs%20require%20bigger%20batteries%2C%20which%20require%20more%20raw%20materials%20to%20manufacture%2C%20which%20requires%20producers%20to%20beef%20up%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-cars-vehicles-solution-climate-change-crisis-dirty-minerals-mining-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenvironmentally%20destructive%20mining%20operations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20bigger%20batteries%20allow%20drivers%20to%20travel%20farther%20between%20charges%2C%20they%20also%20make%20the%20cars%20heavier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iihs.org%2Fnews%2Fdetail%2Fas-heavy-evs-proliferate-their-weight-may-be-a-drag-on-safety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20dangerous%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20worse%20for%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Brange%20anxiety%26quot%3B%20that%20has%20resulted%20in%20massive%20batteries%20is%20another%20reason%20EVs%20don't%20work%20as%20a%20replacement%20for%20gas%20cars.%20Niedermeyer%20said%20that%20while%20an%20electric%20car%20can%20meet%20most%20people's%20driving%20needs%2C%20it%20struggles%20with%20edge%20cases%20like%20road%20trips%20because%20of%20the%20need%20to%20recharge.%20Since%20Americans%20have%20been%20promised%20a%20one-to-one%20substitute%20for%20their%20gas%20cars%2C%20this%20seems%20like%20a%20failure%3B%20an%20EV%20should%20be%20able%20to%20do%20everything%20a%20gas%20car%20can.%20This%20idea%20persists%20even%20though%20in%202023%20the%20average%20US%20driver%20traveled%20only%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F08%2F27%2Fopinion%2Felectric-car-battery-range.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E40%20miles%20a%20day%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%202022%20about%2093%25%20of%20US%20trips%20were%20less%20than%2030%20miles.%20Still%2C%20in%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20Ipsos%20last%20fall%2C%2073%25%20of%20respondents%20indicated%20they%20had%20concerns%20about%20EV%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20focus%20on%20increasing%20EVs'%20range%20is%20contributing%20to%20their%20relatively%20high%20prices.%20Unlike%20with%20gas%20cars%2C%20the%20more%20you%20pay%20for%20an%20EV%2C%20the%20more%20range%20you%20can%20expect%20to%20receive.%20And%20since%20Americans%20have%20been%20conditioned%20to%20want%20a%20lot%20of%20range%2C%20cars%20with%20big%20batteries%20and%20longer%20ranges%20have%20dominated%20the%20market%2C%20resulting%20in%20stubbornly%20high%20prices.%20In%20September%2C%20Cox%20Automotive%20pegged%20the%20average%20EV%20price%20at%20%2450%2C683%2C%20down%2022%25%20from%20the%20same%20time%20last%20year.%20But%20an%20analysis%20from%20CarGurus%20found%20that%20EV%20prices%20were%20still%2028%25%20higher%20than%20gas-vehicle%20prices%20on%20average.%20With%20prices%20for%20everything%20else%20%E2%80%94%20rent%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20other%20goods%20%E2%80%94%20increasing%2C%20the%20average%20person%20has%20less%20cash%20to%20splurge%20on%20an%20expensive%20electric%20vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20means%20there's%20a%20natural%20limit%20to%20the%20number%20of%20American%20households%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20make%20the%20shift%20to%20electric.%20They've%20largely%20been%20high-income%20households%20in%20places%20like%20California%2C%20where%20charging%20infrastructure%20is%20more%20plentiful.%20The%20polling%20firm%20Strategic%20Vision%20found%20that%20EV%20buyers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F23934889%2Felectric-vehicle-ev-transition-sales-delays-politics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20median%20household%20income%20of%20%24186%2C000%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cox%20estimated%20that%208%25%20to%209%25%20of%20new-vehicle%20sales%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%202023%20would%20be%20electric%2C%20but%20getting%20above%20that%20threshold%20is%20proving%20to%20be%20more%20difficult%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Norway%20model%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20any%20direct%20inspiration%20for%20the%20United%20States'%20EV%20policy%2C%20it's%20Norway.%20As%20the%20story%20goes%2C%20Norway%20introduced%20some%20compelling%20subsidies%20for%20EVs%2C%20sales%20took%20off%2C%20and%20now%20the%20vehicles%20virtually%20dominate%20the%20roads.%20But%20the%20reality%20isn't%20so%20simple.%20And%20Norway's%20challenges%20bode%20poorly%20for%20America's%20EV%20push.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorway%20introduced%20EV%20incentives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Ffuture-perfect%2F23939076%2Fnorway-electric-vehicle-cars-evs-tesla-oslo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20the%201990s%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20added%20more%20when%20EV%20technology%20really%20took%20off%20in%20the%202010s.%20EV%20drivers%20could%20get%20perks%20like%20free%20parking%2C%20permission%20to%20drive%20in%20bus%20lanes%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20exemptions%20from%20taxes%20and%20fees%20that%20could%20ultimately%20save%20them%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20In%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcleantechnica.com%2F2023%2F10%2F04%2Fnorways-evs-at-a-record-93-share%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E87%25%20of%20new-vehicle%20sales%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20fully%20electric%20vehicles.%20The%20problem%2C%20Ketan%20Joshi%2C%20a%20climate-analysis%20expert%20in%20Oslo%2C%20told%20me%2C%20is%20that%20that%20stat%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20really%20give%20you%20a%20good%20picture%20of%20the%20rate%20of%20change.%26quot%3B%20Though%20the%20new-vehicle%20sales%20figure%20is%20high%2C%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssb.no%2Fen%2Ftransport-og-reiseliv%2Flandtransport%2Fstatistikk%2Fbilparken%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efrom%20Statistics%20Norway%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20the%20total%20share%20of%20EVs%20on%20Norwegian%20roads%20in%202022%20was%20only%20about%2020%25%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20still%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20until%20everyone's%20driving%20electric.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20this%20shift%2C%20Norway%20isn't%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimateactiontracker.org%2Fcountries%2Fnorway%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2030%20emissions-reduction%20targets%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20emissions%20from%20passenger%20vehicles%20have%20fallen%20slightly%2C%20Joshi%20said%2C%20those%20reductions%20are%20being%20canceled%20out%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20emissions%20from%20trucks.%20People%20in%20Norway%20own%20more%20cars%20than%20they%20have%20in%20the%20past%2C%20in%20part%20because%20EV%20incentives%20encourage%20people%20to%20buy%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20cars%2C%20and%20the%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Ffuture-perfect%2F23939076%2Fnorway-electric-vehicle-cars-evs-tesla-oslo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eno%20plans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20reduce%20how%20much%20people%20are%20driving.%20The%20researcher%20Benjamin%20Sovacool%20and%20his%20colleagues%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0921800918307602%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20just%20like%20in%20the%20US%2C%20EV%20buyers%20in%20Norway%20%26quot%3Btend%20to%20be%20in%20higher%20income%20brackets%2C%20often%20using%20their%20EV%20as%20a%20second%20car.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Norwegian%20approach%20has%20also%20had%20a%20ton%20of%20unintended%20consequences.%20Joshi%20told%20me%20that%20the%20decline%20in%20gas%20tax%20revenue%20due%20to%20EV%20adoption%20had%20triggered%20a%20contentious%20political%20debate%20about%20increasing%20road%20tolls%20to%20make%20up%20the%20difference.%20(A%20political%20party%20was%20even%20formed%20on%20the%20platform%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2019%2Fsep%2F08%2Froad-rage-norway-goes-to-polls-split-over-environmental-policies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estopping%20the%20tolls%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20Plus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frobbieandrew.github.io%2FEV%2Fimg%2Fweight_by_drivetrain_smoothed.svg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eheavier%20electric%20vehicles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20harder%20on%20roads%2C%20produce%20more%20air%20pollution%2C%20and%20pose%20a%20greater%20safety%20risk%20for%20pedestrians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorway%20has%20made%20great%20headway%20in%20getting%20buyers%20to%20go%20for%20EVs%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20silver%20bullet%2C%20especially%20on%20a%20short%20timeline.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20you%20the%20extreme%20slowness%20of%20transition%20that%20is%20basically%20guided%20by%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20people%20buy%20a%20new%20car%2C%26quot%3B%20Joshi%20said%20of%20Norway's%20approach.%20Reducing%20transportation%20emissions%20by%20incentivizing%20people%20to%20replace%20their%20car%20with%20an%20EV%20is%20incredibly%20slow.%20And%20for%20countries%20like%20the%20US%20that%20got%20started%20late%2C%20it's%20a%20warning%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorway%20shows%20that%20if%20US%20policymakers%20stick%20with%20the%20current%20model%20of%20EV%20transition%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20difficult%20road.%20Even%20if%20adoption%20keeps%20ticking%20up%2C%20it%20will%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20get%20existing%20internal-combustion-engine%20vehicles%20off%20the%20road%20and%20see%20a%20notable%20decline%20in%20transport%20emissions.%20Plus%2C%20there%20will%20be%20other%20issues%20to%20deal%20with%20like%20increased%20road%20maintenance%20and%20pedestrian%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNarrow%20success%20in%20one%20area%20is%20not%20something%20you%20necessarily%20want%20to%20emulate%2C%26quot%3B%20Joshi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETime%20for%20a%20rethink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20from%20gas-powered%20cars%20to%20electric%20vehicles%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20rethink%20how%20Americans%20get%20from%20place%20to%20place.%20But%20so%20far%20the%20US%20government%2C%20carmakers%2C%20and%20consumers%20have%20been%20pursuing%20a%20small-minded%20swap%20that%20lacks%20the%20necessary%20ambition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20Americans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-vehicles-wont-save-us-get-rid-of-cars-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Editch%20driving%20altogether%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20to%20reduce%20emissions%2C%20but%20it%20would%20require%20a%20massive%20rethink%20of%20our%20transport%20system.%20Something%20like%20that%20doesn't%20happen%20overnight%2C%20and%20given%20the%20decadeslong%20lack%20of%20investment%20in%20anything%20other%20than%20car%20infrastructure%2C%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20other%20opportunities%20for%20a%20better%20future.%20If%20the%20government%20and%20automakers%20are%20serious%20about%20making%20transportation%20more%20sustainable%2C%20they%20should%20be%20incentivizing%20smaller%20vehicles%2C%20hybrid%20cars%2C%20and%20public%20transportation%20like%20trains%20and%20buses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEVs%20can%20be%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20fight%20against%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20but%20America's%20EV%20plan%20needs%20to%20lean%20into%20what%20these%20cars%20do%20well%3A%20short%20daily%20trips%20that%20can%20be%20taken%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-chinese-electric-cars-will-upend-the-us-vehicle-market-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esmall%2C%20affordable%20cars%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20who%20frequently%20take%20long%20trips%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20hybrid%20cars.%20And%20better%20public%20transit%20and%20faster%20intercity%20trains%20could%20make%20a%20huge%20difference%20for%20people%20and%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20be%20a%20sexy%20and%20industry-friendly%20approach%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis%