ndrew-yeung-google-employee-throwing-techs-hottest-parties-new-york-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20parties%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20writes%20that%20he%20was%20able%20to%20secure%20promotions%20quickly%20by%20learning%20to%C2%A0'eat%20the%20frog'%20for%20his%20boss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20figured%20out%20which%20tasks%20his%20manager%20didn't%20like%20doing%20and%20took%20them%20off%20their%20plates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20job%20was%20at%20a%20global%20advertising%20agency%20with%20over%2020%2C000%20employees.%20I%20went%20from%20being%20an%20intern%2C%20still%20in%20school%2C%20to%20working%20directly%20with%20the%20CEO%20and%20Chief%20Strategy%20Officer%20in%20under%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20a%20way%20to%20go%20above%20and%20beyond%20in%20my%20role%20by%20identifying%20niche%20problems%20and%20solving%20them%20to%20build%20trust%20with%20my%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20always%20%26quot%3Beat%20the%20frog%26quot%3B%20for%20my%20manager.%20I%20identify%20the%20work%20my%20manager%20dislikes%2C%20such%20as%20performing%20administrative%20work%2C%20and%20get%20it%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20simple%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20your%20current%20job%20well%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EIdentify%20the%20work%20your%20manager%20dislikes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ELearn%20how%20to%20do%20them%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20them%20well%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20at%20Meta%2C%20there%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20step%20in%20to%20do%20the%20operationally%20rigorous%2C%20day-to-day%20project%20management.%20Everyone%20loved%20doing%20the%20shiny%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20the%20strategy%20and%20project%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20nobody%20wanted%20to%20do%20the%20operational%20coordination%2C%20so%20I%20did.%20This%20helped%20me%20build%20a%20name%20for%20myself%20for%20being%20an%20excellent%20operations%20person%2C%20and%20I%20got%20promoted%20within%2018%20months%20of%20joining%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20at%20Google%2C%20our%20team%20was%20responsible%20for%20building%20products%20and%20tools%20for%20sales%20teams.%20One%20thing%20our%20team%20had%20to%20do%20that%20was%20crucial%20to%20the%20business%20(but%20was%20not%20considered%20particularly%20exciting)%2C%20was%20the%20ongoing%20maintenance%20of%20the%20dashboards%20that%20powered%20the%20analytics%20behind%20the%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20everyone%20loved%20product%20design%20and%20strategy%2C%20but%20few%20wanted%20to%20do%20the%20backend%20data%20work.%20I%20volunteered%20to%20take%20on%20this%20work%20from%20my%20manager%20and%2C%20over%20time%2C%20built%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20team%20player%20who%20could%20step%20in%20where%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFour%20steps%20to%20eat%20the%20frog%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Do%20your%20current%20job%20well%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFirst%2C%20you%20must%20do%20the%20baseline%20job%20well.%20If%20you're%20a%20data%20analyst%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20doing%20the%20data%20analytics%20job%20pretty%20well.%20If%20you're%20in%20sales%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20selling.%20And%20if%20you're%20in%20project%20management%2C%20you%20need%20to%20ensure%20all%20the%20projects%20are%20well-managed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20properly%20onboarded%20to%20a%20role%20usually%20takes%20four%20to%20six%20months.%20Meta%20was%20my%20first%20foray%20into%20Big%20Tech%2C%20so%20it%20took%20about%20eight%20months.%20Google%20was%20fairly%20quick%2C%20though%2C%20as%20I%20had%20already%20done%20the%20tech%20thing.%20When%20I%20was%20onboarded%20and%20had%20learned%20how%20to%20do%20the%20job%20well%2C%20I%20would%20try%20to%20do%20it%20faster%20or%20automate%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20I%20delivered%20a%20lot%20of%20presentations%20to%20executives.%20The%20first%20presentation%20I%20created%20took%20around%2020%20hours.%20It%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20lot%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20coordination%20and%20manual%20work%20was%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I%20made%20extra%20effort%20to%20improve%20my%20ability%20to%20make%20high-quality%20presentations%20quickly%20(which%20involved%20skills%20like%20storytelling%2C%20graphic%20design%2C%20and%20copywriting)%2C%20and%20I%20reduced%20the%20time%20to%20five%20hours.%20At%20Google%2C%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20a%20product%20brief%20I%20ever%20created%20initially%20took%20me%2015%20hours%2C%20and%20using%20the%20same%20principles%2C%20I%20reduced%20it%20to%20five%20hours%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20always%20try%20to%20improve%20the%20speed%20of%20completing%20the%20work%20without%20compromising%20quality.%20This%20would%20free%20up%20time%20and%20headspace%2C%20which%20I%20would%20allocate%20to%20new%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Identify%20the%20work%20your%20manager%20dislikes%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOnce%20you%20have%20the%20bandwidth%20to%20take%20on%20new%20projects%2C%20start%20to%20observe%20your%20manager%20(or%20leadership%20team)%20for%20opportunities%20to%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20yourself%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20they%20spend%20their%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20are%20their%20top%20priorities%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20do%20they%20like%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20do%20they%20not%20like%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20bucket%20is%20an%20easy%2C%20low-effort%20opportunity%20for%20you%20to%20get%20involved%20and%20deliver%20immediate%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Learn%20how%20to%20do%20those%20tasks%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAsk%20questions%2C%20shadow%20others%2C%20and%20read%20the%20documentation%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20do%20the%20specific%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETry%20not%20to%20bother%20your%20manager%20too%20much%20(the%20whole%20point%20is%20to%20take%20work%20%3Cem%3Eoff%3C%2Fem%3E%20their%20plate)%2C%20but%20if%20you%20have%20to%2C%20sell%20the%20vision%20of%20what%20you%20hope%20to%20accomplish%3A%20to%20reduce%20their%20workload%20in%20the%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20done%20that%2C%20remember%20to%20document%20everything%20to%20create%20a%20playbook.%20Do%20this%20by%20noting%20each%20step%20required%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20task.%20Imagine%20you%20have%20to%20teach%20someone%20else%20how%20to%20do%20the%20activity%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Do%20them%20well%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOnce%20you've%20learned%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20the%20activity%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20execute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApply%20the%20rigor%20that%20you%20would%20to%20the%20other%20aspects%20of%20your%20job.%20Don't%20compromise%20on%20quality%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20sure%20your%20core%20work%20does%20not%20suffer%20from%20taking%20on%20new%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEating%20the%20frog%20ultimately%20builds%20trust%20and%20credibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20replicated%20this%20framework%20to%20accelerate%20promotions%20throughout%20my%20career%2C%20at%20companies%20like%20Meta%20and%20up%20until%20my%20last%20role%20as%20a%20global%20product%20lead%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20I've%20advised%20and%20coached%20many%20early%20career%20professionals%20in%20product%20management%2C%20business%20strategy%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20operations.%20They've%20all%20adopted%20this%20framework%20to%20see%20a%20massive%20positive%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEat%20the%20frog%20for%20your%20manager%20to%20build%20trust%20and%20credibility%2C%20so%20that%20when%20the%20time%20comes%20for%20a%20promotion%20or%20raise%2C%20your%20manager%20will%20step%20up%20to%20the%20plate%20for%20you.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EAndrew%20Yeung%20is%20a%20former%20Meta%20and%20Google%20employee%20who%20now%20throws%20tech%20parties%20through%20