2F106514218.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20software%20engineer%20ranks%20his%20top%2010%20hardest%20interviews%20after%20landing%2018%20offers%20from%20tech%20companies%20like%20Apple%2C%20Palantir%2C%20and%20Meta%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221872%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steven%20Zhang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65846d9ca79e5746976c5226%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221404%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZhang%20ranks%20the%2010%20most%20difficult%20software%20engineering%20interviews.%3Cp%3ESteven%20Zhang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESteven%20Zhang%20is%20a%20former%20software%20engineer%20at%20Airtable.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBefore%20landing%20the%20job%2C%20he%20began%20his%20job%20search%20in%202019%20and%20received%2018%20offers%20after%2022%20interviews.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere%20is%20his%20ranking%20of%20the%2010%20most%20difficult%20interviews%20he'd%20gone%20through%2C%20including%20Google%2C%20Uber.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20in%202014%20and%20currently%20manage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climatetechlist.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimateTechList.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20job%20board%20and%20resource%20for%20climate%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20five%20years%20at%20Tableau%2C%20I%20became%20curious%20about%20the%20job%20market%20and%20the%20types%20of%20roles%20available%20at%20various%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202019%2C%20I%20did%20an%20extensive%20job%20search.%20Ultimately%2C%20I%20received%2018%20job%20offers%20after%2022%20on-site%20interviews%20from%20companies%20like%20Apple%2C%20Meta%2C%20Airbnb%2C%20and%20Uber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2022%20companies%20I%20interviewed%20with%2C%20here%20is%20my%20ranking%20of%20the%2010%20most%20difficult%20interviews%20I%20went%20through.%20I%20ranked%20the%20difficulty%20of%20the%20interviews%20based%20on%20three%20factors%3A%20the%20number%20of%20questions%20asked%20within%20a%20time%20limit%2C%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20problems%2C%20and%20the%20novelty%20of%20the%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E10.%20Palantir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20was%20pretty%20standard%20and%20involved%20live%20coding%20and%20system%20design%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interesting%20part%20was%20candidates%20were%20asked%20to%20eat%20lunch%20with%20current%20employees%20and%20other%20candidates.%20It%20was%20a%20bit%20confusing%2C%20and%20although%20the%20recruiter%20said%20the%20lunch%20wasn't%20an%20evaluation%2C%20I%20somehow%20felt%20like%20it%20was.%20Eating%20lunch%20with%20candidates%20was%20also%20a%20bit%20weird%20since%20I%20wondered%20whether%20I%20was%20competing%20against%20this%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Airtable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20take-home%20assignment%20that%20took%20over%20four%20hours%20to%20complete%2C%20but%20they%20paid%20me%20for%20it.%20The%20challenging%20part%20was%20writing%20the%20code%20and%20making%20it%20very%20readable.%20During%20the%20interview%2C%20I%20also%20had%20to%20present%20my%20work%20in%20an%20hourlong%20session%20to%20a%20panel%20of%20two%20or%20three%20interviewers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20liked%20my%20interview%20experience%20at%20Airtable%20and%20ended%20up%20joining%20the%20company.%20It%20was%20a%20small%20company%20then%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20I%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20talk%20to%20leadership%20like%20the%20CTO%2C%20which%20was%20very%20nice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Google%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20algorithm%20questions%20were%20more%20complex%20than%20Airtable's%20and%20Palantir's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonally%2C%20I%20thought%20Google's%20interview%20process%20was%20the%20most%20outdated%20one%20compared%20to%20others%20on%20this%20list.%20I%20only%20wrote%20code%20on%20the%20whiteboard%20and%20didn't%20write%20any%20code%20live%20on%20a%20computer.%20There%20also%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20lack%20of%20coordination%20in%20question%20selection.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20encountered%20similar%20questions%20in%20the%20same%20data%20structure%20niche.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurprisingly%2C%20I%20wasn't%20asked%20any%20behavioral%20questions%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Meta%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Meta%20interview%20was%20surprisingly%20light%2C%20with%20only%20four%20rounds%20compared%20to%20the%20usual%20five%20or%20six%20at%20other%20companies.%20The%20questions%20were%20product-focused%2C%20such%20as%20designing%20a%20live%20commenting%20section%20on%20Facebook%2C%20rather%20than%20purely%20coding-based.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20asking%20the%20recruiter%20why%20the%20interviews%20were%20lighter%20than%20other%20companies%2C%20and%20they%20explained%20that%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20rounds%20didn't%20impact%20the%20quality%20of%20hires%20but%20made%20the%20process%20less%20tiring%20for%20candidates%3B%20they%20could%20also%20spend%20fewer%20company%20resources%20on%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Uber%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tricky%20part%20of%20the%20interview%20was%20that%20so%20many%20tasks%20were%20squeezed%20in%20at%20once%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20have%20time%20to%20receive%20potential%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20know%20whether%20I%20did%20well%20or%20not.%20After%20completing%20the%20first%20part%2C%20we%20quickly%20moved%20to%20part%20two.%20During%20part%20three%2C%20when%20I%20was%20halfway%20done%2C%20they%20announced%20that%20the%20time%20was%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20psychological%20dynamic%20going%20into%20it%20%E2%80%94%20if%20I%20picked%20up%20on%20any%20signal%20on%20how%20I%20was%20doing%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20small%2C%20I%20gained%20some%20momentum%20to%20tackle%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20interview.%20Overall%2C%20it%20was%20a%20pretty%20intense%20interview%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20interesting%20thing%20was%20that%20Uber%20had%20a%20session%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fblog%2Fcleber-cassol%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3BBar%20Raiser%26quot%3B%20interviewers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20session%20brought%20a%20different%20team%20from%20the%20company%20into%20the%20hiring%20process.%20They%20are%20trained%20rigorously%20to%20remove%20any%20biases%20from%20the%20hiring%20process%20and%20ensure%20new%20hires%20surpass%20the%20standard%20set%20by%20other%20peers%20in%20similar%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Cruise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20process%20was%20standard%2C%20including%20algorithm%20and%20system%20design%20questions%20and%20a%20behavioral%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20what%20made%20it%20difficult%20wasn't%20the%20actual%20interview%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20a%20migraine%20during%20the%20interview%20and%20the%20medicine%20didn't%20work.%20This%20was%20a%20lesson%20for%20me%3A%20while%20I%20couldn't%20be%20in%20a%20perfect%20environment%2C%20I%20should%20have%20control%20over%20what%20I%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20rescheduled%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20the%20recruiting%20team%20would%20have%20been%20happy%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Checkr%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coding%20interview%20was%20intense%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20room%20and%20code%20for%20two%20hours%20while%20being%20observed%20and%20questioned%20by%20interviewers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20made%20it%20even%20harder%20was%20I%20had%20to%20write%20a%20fully%20functioning%20piece%20of%20code%2C%20not%20just%20an%20algorithm%2C%20meaning%20the%20code%20had%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Zoox%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZoox%20asks%20intense%20math%20questions%20in%20addition%20to%20standard%20code%20interviews.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20asked%20how%20to%20measure%20the%20distance%20from%20the%20Earth%20to%20the%20Moon%20using%20tools%20like%20a%20protractor%20and%20ruler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20requires%20intensive%20math%20skills%2C%20such%20as%20trigonometry.%20I%20would%20say%20in%20most%20software%20engineering%20interviews%2C%20candidates%20don't%20get%20asked%20about%20these%20kinds%20of%20math%20questions%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Stripe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20diversity%20of%20problems%20made%20the%20interview%20challenging.%20Questions%20ranged%20from%20solving%20bugs%20and%20writing%20code%20using%20an%20existing%20API%20to%20talking%20through%20a%20technical%20design%20without%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20that%2C%20interviews%20at%20Stripe%20are%20much%20more%20of%20a%20real-world%20scenario%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20harder%2C%20too.%20I%20remember%20there%20was%20a%20question%20about%20using%20a%20simplified%20version%20of%20Stripe's%20API%20to%20create%20a%20model%20for%20detecting%20fraud%20in%20orders%20and%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20give%20a%2010%2F10%20rating%20for%20the%20overall%20interview%20process%2C%20though%2C%20because%20I%20felt%20the%20interviewers%20at%20Stripe%20asked%20all%20the%20right%20questions%2C%20and%20the%20interview%20itself%20was%20most%20similar%20to%20what%20a%20real-life%20coding%20experience%20would%20be%20like%20as%20a%20software%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Airbnb%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etwo%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erounds%20of%20technical%20phone%20screens%20and%20an%20on-site%20interview%2C%20where%20they%20asked%20notoriously%20hard%20algorithm%20questions.%20The%20questions%20were%20niche%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20write%20and%20run%20code%20within%2050%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20one%20question%20involved%20a%20rooftop%20with%20a%20unique%20shape%2C%20and%20I%20needed%20to%20estimate%20how%20long%20it%20would%20take%20to%20fill%20it%20with%20water%2C%20considering%20its%20various%20dips%2C%20like%20hills%20and%20valleys.%20For%20a%20question%20like%20this%2C%20I%20had%20to%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20data%20structure%20in%20code%2C%20and%20then%20write%20a%20function%20to%20calculate%20the%20fill-up%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%20also%20went%20two%20levels%20deeper%20in%20behavioral%20rounds%20than%20other%20tech%20companies.%20They%20asked%20me%20about%20projects%20I%20had%20worked%20on%20and%20my%20decision-making%20process.%20The%20pressure%20almost%20made%20me%20feel%20like%20it%20was%20a%20true%20interrogation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Airbnb%20office%20is%20very%20nice%2C%20with%20meeting%20rooms%20that%20resemble%20famous%20Airbnb%20listings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recruiting%20team%20was%20cooperative%20and%20easy%20to%20work%20with%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdjust%20your%20expectations%20in%20today's%20job%20market%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20most%20difficult%20interviews%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20easiest%20ones%20I%20experienced%20were%20WeWork%2C%20Zillow%2C%20and%20Zume.%20However%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20an%20easy%20interview%20necessarily%20indicates%20a%20low%20talent%20bar%20at%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20be%20because%20I%20had%20prepared%20specifically%20for%20the%20questions%20they%20asked%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20my%20experience%20with%20job%20searching%2C%20I%20think%20everyone%20can%20get%20good%20at%20interviewing%20with%20enough%20practice.%20In%20today's%20job%20market%2C%20though%2C%20I%20suggest%20job%20seekers%20adjust%20their%20expectations.%20I%20don't%20think%20I'd%20land%2018%20offers%20today%20because%20the%20hiring%20environment%20is%20so%20competitive%3B%20I'd%20probably%20only%20get%20half%20as%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20crucial%20for%20job%20seekers%20to%20consistently%20tackle%20problems%20every%20day%20and%20operationalize%20their%20job%20search%20process.%20I%20always%20recommend%20maintaining%20a%20calendar%20that%20allows%20recruiters%20to%20schedule%20interviews%20directly%20from%20it%2C%20instead%20of%20emailing%20back%20and%20forth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20think%20it's%20important%20to%20be%20clear%20about%20the%20recruitment%20timeline%20with%20each%20company.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20you're%20consistently%20unable%20to%20get%20past%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20stage%20with%20certain%20companies%2C%20compile%20a%20list%20of%20those%20companies%20and%20try%20to%20get%20introductions%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20work%20in%20Big%20Tech%20and%20want%20to%20share%20your%20experience%2C%20email%20Jennifer%20Eum%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajeum%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejeum%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhardest-software-engineering-interviews-ranked-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704276781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65846d7ecefc010bea264cbb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhardest-software-engineering-interviews-ranked-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20software%20engineer%20who%20received%2018%20job%20offers%20from%20tech%20companies%20like%20Apple%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Palantir%20ranks%20the%20most%20difficult%20interviews.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ayang%40businessinsider.com%20(Aria%20Yang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhardest-software-engineering-interviews-ranked-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Costco's%20CEO%20just%20shared%20a%20surprising%20response%20to%20a%20warehouse%20unionizin