'll%20never%20have%20kids%20for%20various%20reasons.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20one%2C%20she%20has%20medical%20challenges%20that%20she%20doesn't%20want%20to%20pass%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe's%20also%20considered%20the%20cost%20of%20birth%2C%20the%20environmental%20impact%2C%20and%20her%20health.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20millennial%20who%20won't%20have%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20tough%20to%20write%2C%20even%20as%20a%2031-year-old%20who's%20never%20wanted%20kids%2C%20without%20tacking%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bright%20now%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20end.%20It%20feels%20final%20and%20is%20a%20huge%20decision%2C%20but%20I%20have%20a%20clear%20direction%20for%20my%20life%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20choice%20comes%20with%20something%20to%20mourn%20%E2%80%94%20as%20there%20would%20be%20if%20I%20made%20the%20opposite%20choice%20and%20had%20to%20leave%20my%20childless%20life%20behind.%20I%20still%20reserve%20the%20right%20to%20change%20my%20mind%2C%20even%20though%20I%20know%20I%20won't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20take%20the%20decision%20of%20whether%20to%20bring%20a%20new%20life%20into%20this%20world%20lightly.%20I%20respect%20everyone's%20decisions%20for%20their%20own%20families.%20Here's%20why%20I've%20made%20mine%20%E2%80%94%20through%20many%20open%20conversations%20and%20the%20support%20of%20my%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGenetics%20and%20healthcare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffuture-healthcare-dna-genetic-testing-23andme-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGenetic%20testing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20advanced%20a%20lot%20since%20I%20was%20a%20kid%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20and%20that%20knowledge%20is%20power%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20fully%20understand%20that%20I%20was%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20until%20I%20was%2029%20years%20old%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fautism-in-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewomen's%20symptoms%20look%20different%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20recognized%20widely%20when%20I%20was%20growing%20up.%20I%20wasn't%20raised%20to%20think%20neurodiversity%20was%20a%20superpower%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20a%20religious%20upbringing%20and%20was%20homeschooled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20learning%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-autism-surprising-facts-about-autism-spectrum-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20on%20the%20spectrum%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20for%20me%20since%20it's%20so%20different%20for%20everyone.%20When%20I'm%20going%20to%20the%20doctor%20and%20trying%20to%20make%20healthy%20decisions%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20feel%20ready%20to%20go%20through%20a%20pregnancy%20for%20nine%20months%2C%20willingly%20sign%20up%20for%20more%20doctor%20visits%2C%20and%20then%20take%20care%20of%20a%20whole%20new%20person%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20also%20nearly%20blind%20in%20one%20eye%2C%20with%20astigmatism%20in%20the%20other.%20Again%2C%20it's%20genetic%20and%20shared%20by%20many%20of%20my%20relatives.%20The%20optometrist%20told%20me%20that%20with%20today's%20medicine%2C%20this%20could%20be%20fixed%20with%20surgery%20before%20the%20age%20of%205%2C%20in%20case%20I%20wanted%20children%20someday%20(putting%20a%20toddler%20through%20an%20expensive%20surgery%20is%20the%20modern%20option%2C%20I%20suppose).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20more%20that%20I%20deal%20with%2C%20of%20course%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20me%20think%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20put%20someone%20else%20who%20I%20love%20through%20every%20medical%20challenge%20that%20I've%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20genetic%20disorder%20during%20pregnancy%20is%20like%20a%20mixed%20surprise%20bag.%20The%20unknown%20in%20this%20scenario%20%E2%80%94%20with%20uncertain%2C%20expensive%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-american-health-care-system-sucks-2013-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunreliable%20American%20healthcare%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20too%20risky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEthics%20and%20the%20environment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20sources%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanet-warming-carbon-dioxide-levels-highest-human-history-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecarbon%20emissions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20humans.%20From%20a%20Mother%20Earth%20point%20of%20view%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrodies.com%2Finsights%2Ffamily-law%2Fadoption-a-climate-conscious-choice%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewould%20be%20more%20environmentally%20friendly%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20already%20living%20humans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20to%20pop%20out%20new%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20logical%20side%20of%20my%20brain%20says%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fadoption-is-my-first-choice-for-motherhood-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econsidering%20adoption%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20the%20urge%20to%20raise%20someone%20strikes.%20Until%20recently%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20might%20consider%20it%2C%20but%20I'm%20leaning%20away%20from%20it%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EActual%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20hospital%20birth%20is%20very%20pricey.%20Based%20on%20what%20I've%20heard%20from%20my%20peers%20who%20are%20parents%20and%20who%20have%20health%20insurance%2C%20a%20hospital%20birth%20can%20run%20you%20between%20%243%2C000%20and%20%246%2C000%20or%20more%20after%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20or%20up%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fpictures%2Fcost-giving-birth-in-united-states%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOregon%26amp%3Btext%3DIt%2520costs%2520%252415%252C121%252C%2520on%2520average%2Cgive%2520birth%2520in%2520Oregon%2520hospitals.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20%2415%2C000%20without%20insurance%2C%20on%20average%2C%20in%20Oregon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fwhat-is-a-midwife%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadd%20a%20midwife%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20your%20care%20team%20to%20advocate%20for%20you%2C%20but%20they%20can%20also%20be%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20partner%20and%20I%20have%20health%20insurance%20through%20our%20employers%2C%20but%20we've%20been%20between%20coverage%20before.%20Plus%2C%20there%20can%20be%20up%20to%20a%20three-month%20delay%20for%20health%20insurance%20to%20kick%20in%20when%20you%20start%20a%20new%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20factor%20in%20prenatal%20care%2C%20postnatal%20care%2C%20diapers%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20even%20worse%2C%20I'm%20told%20%E2%80%94%20formula%2C%20as%20well%20as%20day%20care%20and%20education.%20Then%20factor%20in%20food%20and%20clothes%20for%20at%20least%2018%20years.%20The%20US%20average%20for%20all%20that%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fhow-much-does-it-cost-to-raise-a-child-240000%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Equarter%20million%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20one%20child%20in%20average%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20before%20college.%20That's%20with%20no%20nanny%20to%20help%20with%20day%20care%20and%20no%20trust%20fund.%20That's%20without%20factoring%20in%20personal%20time%20doing%20everything%20necessary%20to%20be%20a%20parent.%20The%20cost%20is%20just%20too%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersonal%20health%20and%20healthcare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20maternal%20mortality%20rate%20in%20the%20US%20is%2032.9%20maternal%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%2C%20and%20it's%20even%20higher%20for%20women%20of%20color%20(69.9%20per%20100%2C000).%20That's%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5575578%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C