ompanies%2Fnews%2Fpetronet-to-sign-deal-to-extend-qatar-lng-imports-beyond-2028-oil-secy-124010300531_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpetronet-to-sign-deal-to-extend-qatar-lng-imports-beyond-2028-oil-secy-124010300531_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpetronet-to-sign-deal-to-extend-qatar-lng-imports-beyond-2028-oil-secy-124010300531_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'One%20waits%20for%20coronation%20but%20...'%3A%20Chouhan%20turns%20emotional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704273339000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106511938%2Cimgsize-36388.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsometimes-one-waits-for-coronation-but-ends-up-in-exile-ex-mp-cm-shivraj-chouhan-turns-emotional%2Farticleshow%2F106511873.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20turned%20emotional%20while%20addressing%20his%20supporters%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20saying%20that%20sometimes%20one%20waits%20for%20%26quot%3Brajtilak%26quot%3B%20(coronation)%20but%20ends%20up%20in%20%26quot%3Bvanvas%26quot%3B%20(exile).Chouhan%2C%20who%20was%20addressing%20a%20gathering%20in%20Shahganj%20town%20under%20his%20Budhni%20assembly%20seat%20on%20January%202%2C%20promised%20that%20he%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20among%20the%20people%2C%20especially%20his%20sisters.The%20four-time%20chief%20minister%2C%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20BJP's%20landslide%20victory%20in%20the%20recent%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20elections%2C%20had%20to%20make%20way%20for%20Mohan%20Yadav%20last%20month%20after%20the%20party%20decided%20to%20go%20for%20a%20new%20line%20of%20leadership%20in%20the%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20A%20First%2C%20India%20To%20Launch%20Its%20Satellite%20On%20SpaceX's%20Falcon-9%20Rocket%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20space%20agency%20will%20rely%20on%20SpaceX%20to%20launch%20its%20next%20generation%20heavy%20communications%20satellite%20named%20GSAT-20.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20Department%20of%20Space%20and%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organization%20(ISRO)%20will%20use%20the%20Falcon-9%20heavy%20lift%20launcher%20which%20may%20liftoff%20from%20Florida%20on%20a%20dedicated%20Indian%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20also%20exposes%20the%20weak%20underbelly%20of%20ISRO%20which%20still%20lacks%20a%20rocket%20which%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20lift%20big%20communication%20satellites.%20ISRO%20Chairman%20S%20Somanath%20ISRO%20says%20India%20had%20to%20go%20to%20SpaceX%20since%20'no%20other%20rocket%20was%20available%20in%20time.'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commercial%20arm%20or%20ISRO%2C%20New%20Space%20India%20Limited%20has%20signed%20a%20contract%20with%20SpaceX%20for%20a%20possible%20liftoff%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year.%20The%20SpaceX%20deal%20also%20signifies%20a%20significant%20shift%20since%20till%20now%20India%20relied%20heavily%20on%20the%20France%20led%20Arianespace%20consortium%20to%20launch%20the%20heavy%20satellites.%20India's%20own%20rockets%20lack%20the%20capacity%20for%20launching%20very%20heavy%20satellites%20to%20the%20geostationary%20orbit%20beyond%204%20ton%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NSIL%2C%20GSAT-20%20offers%20Ka-Ka%20band%20high%20through%20put%20(HTS)%20capacity%20with%2032%20beams%20having%20Pan-India%20coverage%20including%20Andaman%20%26amp%3B%20Nicobar%2C%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20and%20Lakshadweep%20islands.%20NSIL%20is%20realizing%20GSAT-20%20satellite%20through%20ISRO.%C2%A0%20The%20satellite%20weighs%204700%20kg%2C%20offers%20HTS%20capacity%20of%20nearly%2048Gpbs.%20The%20satellite%20has%20been%20specifically%20designed%20to%20meet%20the%20demanding%20service%20needs%20of%20remote%2F%20unconnected%20regions.%20Dr%20Radhakrishnan%20Durairaj%2C%20CMD%2C%20NSIL%20says%20this%20is%20the%20second%20demand%20driven%20communication%20satellite%20mission%20being%20undertaken%20by%20NSIL%20after%20the%20GSAT-24%20mission%20whose%20full%20capacity%20was%20leased%20out%20to%20Tata%20Play.%20Durairaj%20says%20this%20new%20satellite%20deal%20only%20confirms%20that%20the%20reform%20process%20undertaken%20by%20the%20government%20is%20yielding%20results.%20NSIL%20has%20not%20revealed%20who%20has%20bought%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20satellite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20France%20and%20Arianespace%20was%20indeed%20a%20trusted%20all%20weather%20partner%20all%20along%20and%20India%20launched%2023%20of%20its%20heavy%20duty%20communications%20satellites%20on%20this%20rocket%20owned%20by%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency.%20Durairaj%20says%20but%20for%20a%2021%20st%20century%20new%20age%20public%20sector%20undertaking%20looking%20at%20bottom%20lines%20%60if%20commercials%20and%20readiness%20make%20sense%20we%20go%20for%20it'.%20It%20must%20also%20be%20acknowledged%20that%20Arianespace%20retired%20its%20most%20trusted%20rocket%20Ariane-5%20and%20the%20replacement%20Ariane-6%20has%20been%20much%20delayed.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20GSAT%2020%20satellite%20will%20now%20be%20renamed%20GSAT-N2%20and%20it%20will%20essentially%20provide%20broadband%20internet%20access%20to%20remote%20areas.%20This%20will%20obviously%20be%20in%20competition%20with%20OneWeb%20and%20Starlink%20who%20may%20get%20licenses%20soon%20since%20the%20new%20Telecom%20law%20paves%20way%20for%20them%20to%20launch%20their%20services.%20Other%20players%20actively%20wooing%20the%20space%20based%20internet%20service%20provider%20market%20is%20Reliance%20Jiospace.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20heaviest%20rocket%20dubbed%20the%20Bahuballi%20or%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark%203%20can%20lift%20only%204000%20kilogram%20satellites%20to%20the%20geo-stationary%20orbit.%20Mr.%20S%20Somanath%20has%20been%20stressing%20the%20need%20to%20urgently%20build%20a%20heavier%20rocket%20called%20the%20Next%20Generation%20Launch%20Vehicle%20(NGLV)%20which%20can%20lift%20up%20to%2010%2C000%20kilograms%20to%20the%20same%20orbit%2C%20it%20is%20already%20being%20designed%20at%20the%20Vikram%20Sarabhai%20Space%20Center%20and%20will%20take%20few%20more%20years%20to%20become%20a%20reality.%20Somanath%20says%20%60India's%20launch%20capability%20has%20to%20be%20enhanced%20to%20meet%20future%20needs%2C%20while%20being%20cost%20competitive'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704273180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-11%2Fq9cms5ao_spacex-falcon-9-rocket-650_625x300_11_November_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-a-first-india-to-launch-its-satellite-on-spacexs-falcon-9-rocket-4792333%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Indian%20space%20agency%20will%20rely%20on%20SpaceX%20to%20launch%20its%20next%20generation%20heavy%20communications%20satellite%20named%20GSAT-20.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-a-first-india-to-launch-its-satellite-on-spacexs-falcon-9-rocket-4792333%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-a-first-india-to-launch-its-satellite-on-spacexs-falcon-9-rocket-4792333%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-a-first-india-to-launch-its-satellite-on-spacexs-falcon-9-rocket-4792333%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20Political%20Repression%20and%20Economic%20Crisis%2C%20Bangladesh%20is%20Set%20for%20a%20One-Sided%20Election%20on%20Jan%207%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03144455%2FEffect-52.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20period%20of%20economic%20boom%20and%20political%20tranquility.%20There%20are%20shiny%20new%20buildings%2C%20expressways%2C%20and%20bridges.%20Shopping%20malls%20abound%20with%20imported%20luxury%20brands.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20dark%20spots%20%E2%80%93inequality%20is%20rising%2C%20and%20dissent%20is%20stifled.%20But%20these%20are%20ignored%20in%20the%20superficially%20laudatory%20articles%20in%20the%20foreign%20media.%20Meanwhile%2C%20foreign%20financiers%20lend%20to%20the%20country%20willingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%2C%20of%20course%2C%20things%20change.%20And%20they%20change%20rather%20quickly.%20All%20those%20things%20that%20were%20glossed%20over%20previously%20suddenly%20loom%20large.%20Turns%20out%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20banks%20are%20saddled%20with%20bad%20loans%20issued%20to%20politically%20connected%20cronies%20and%20crooks.%20The%20currency%20tanks.%20Inflation%20soars.%20With%20peaceful%20democratic%20avenues%20closed%2C%20a%20spasm%20of%20violence%20ensues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%2C%20banking%20sector%20woes%2C%20and%20authoritarian%20politics%20make%20for%20a%20volatile%20cocktail%20that%20is%20redolent%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%20of%20the%20mid-1990s%20%E2%80%93%20but%20as%20things%20stand%2C%20they%20also%20describe%20a%20Bangladesh%20of%20the%20mid-2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20consider%20each%20of%20these%20elements%20in%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Bangladesh%20has%20become%20a%20capital%20importer%2C%20running%20a%20current%20account%20deficit%20even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20And%2C%20according%20to%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20(IMF%E2%80%99s)%20latest%20assessment%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20the%20deficit%20is%20likely%20to%20persist%20well%20into%20the%20late%202020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20nation%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20reflects%20the%20difference%20between%20its%20aggregate%20savings%20and%20investment%2C%20with%20a%20deficit%20signifying%20inadequate%20savings%20to%20meet%20its%20investment%20needs.%20With%20around%2030%25%20of%20GDP%20saved%2C%20the%20savings%20rate%20in%20Bangladesh%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20low%20%E2%80%93%20by%20way%20of%20comparison%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20savings%20rate%20has%20tended%20to%20be%20around%2015%25%20of%20GDP.%20Rather%2C%20as%20Chart%201%20shows%2C%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20deficit%20reflects%20a%20strong%20investment%20boom%20before%20the%20pandemic%20that%20is%20set%20to%20resume%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22929%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%20929w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2-300x186.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691395%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22575%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20Chart%202%20shows%20that%20while%20private%20investment%20is%20set%20to%20recover%20to%20the%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20relative%20to%20GDP%2C%20shaking%20off%20recent%20woes%2C%20public%20investment%20is%20projected%20to%20scale%20new%20heights%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%20Of%20course%2C%20in%20and%20of%20itself%2C%20this%20is%20very%20sensible.%20Bangladesh%20is%20a%20developing%20country%20desperately%20in%20need%20of%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20roads%2C%20railways%2C%20electricity%20generation%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20There%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20financing%20some%20of%20these%20projects%20from%20external%20sources%2C%20provided%20the%20projects%20are%20well%20governed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20elements%20to%20this.%20First%2C%20financing%20of%20many%20of%20these%20projects%20is%20quite%20one-sided%20against%20Bangladeshi%20taxpayers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froadtodemocracy.com%2F2023%2F03%2F20%2Fadani-group-awami-league-nexus%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20power%20purchase%20agreement%20with%20the%20Adani%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20a%20particularly%20egregious%2C%20but%20far%20from%20the%20only%2C%20example.%20Second%2C%20these%20projects%20are%20usually%20implemented%20with%20woeful%20management%2C%20resulting%20in%20significant%20cost%20overruns.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbdnews24.com%2Feconomy%2Fbangladesh-infrastructure-is-worlds-costliest-says-world-bank%5C%22%3Einfrastructure%20projects%20were%20among%20the%20costliest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%20may%20well%20have%20an%20upside%20to%20it%2C%20at%20least%20theoretically%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20positive%20about%20a%20wobbly%20banking%20sector.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20banking%20sector%20is%20saddled%20with%20non-performing%20loans%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20borrower%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20interest%20or%20principal%20payments%20for%20an%20extended%20period.%20Chart%203%20shows%20that%20the%20problem%20is%20particularly%20acute%20in%20the%20state-owned%20banks%2C%20which%20are%20also%20not%20well%20capitalised%20(Chart%204)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20they%20are%20not%20well%20placed%20to%20cover%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20their%20lending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22951%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%20951w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4-300x179.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691397%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22567%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20governance%20problems%20around%20the%20infrastructure%20megaprojects%20as%20well%20as%20the%20woes%20in%20the%20banking%20sector%20ultimately%20point%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20authoritarian%20political%20economy%20whereby%20the%20ruling%20regime%2C%20instead%20of%20governing%20with%20a%20mandate%20from%20the%20voters%2C%20has%20been%20relying%20on%20the%20support%20of%20powerful%20oligarchs%20who%20are%20given%20access%20to%20loans%20and%20opportunities%20without%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChart%205%20shows%20the%20regression%20of%20electoral%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20using%20the%20V-Dem%20index.%20This%20index%20captures%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20governments%20are%20elected%20under%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20with%20guaranteed%20freedom%20of%20association%20and%20expression.%20Countries%20are%20given%20a%20score%20between%200%20and%201%2C%20the%20latter%20being%20most%20democratic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Bangladesh%20had%20a%20score%20of%200.27%2C%20compared%20with%200.4%20in%20India%20and%200.39%20in%20Pakistan.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20slide%20to%20authoritarianism%20reflects%20a%20one-sided%20election%20in%20January%202014%20where%20the%20incumbent%20Awami%20League%20won%20153%20seats%20out%20of%20300%20unopposed%2C%20and%20a%20blatantly%20rigged%20election%20in%20December%202018%20when%20ballot%20boxes%20were%20stuffed%20the%20night%20before%20the%20polling%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22857%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5.jpg%20857w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5-300x164.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691399%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%E2%80%99s%20turn%20towards%20a%20dictatorship%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20third%20consecutive%20one-sided%20election%20on%20January%207%20%E2%80%93%20the%20opposition%20parties%20are%20boycotting%20the%20election%20in%20light%20of%20their%20past%20experience%20as%20well%20as%20the%20fact%20that%20over%2020%2C000%20of%20their%20members%20have%20been%20interned%20since%20late%20October%20through%20a%20draconian%20crackdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20may%20look%20unassailable%20politically.%20But%20so%20did%20President%20Suharto%20of%20Indonesia%20in%201996.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20nostrum%20pushed%20by%20authoritarian%20leaders%20that%20they%20can%20make%20the%20tough%20decisions%20needed%20to%20address%20economic%20challenges%2C%20experiences%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20(and%20indeed%20in%20many%20other%20countries%20around%20the%20world)%20suggest%20that%20authoritarian%20regimes%20with%20poorly%20governed%20banking%20sectors%20and%20mega%20projects%20often%20end%20up%20in%20significant%20political%20and%20economic%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20making%20tough%20decisions%20and%20taking%20on%20the%20vested%20interests%2C%20authoritarian%20regimes%20relied%20on%20the%20very%20same%20vested%20interests%20for%20their%20survival.%20The%20resulting%20cronyism%20only%20exacerbated%20the%20crisis%2C%20not%20resolved%20it.%20In%20Thailand%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Asian%20Financial%20Crisis%20of%201997%20was%20followed%20by%20years%20of%20political%20conflict%20and%20economic%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBang