0administration%20and%20a%20dignified%20process%20of%20governance.%20An%20inability%20to%20ensure%20one%20would%20naturally%20affect%20the%20other.%20In%20theory%2C%20all%20this%20can%20make%20sense%20in%20a%20country%20where%20governance%20is%20aligned%20with%20principles%20of%20constitutional%20and%20civic-institutional%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20if%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20case%20in%20actuality%20(as%20we%20see%20in%20the%20current%20context).%20What%20if%20a%20state%20decides%20to%20create%20laws%20for%20implementation%20that%20involve%20the%20creation%20of%20targets%20and%20polarise%20society%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20legislative%20bulldozing%20has%20coercively%20institutionalised%20a%20process%20of%20non-consultative%20law-making%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20just%20create%20targets%2C%20or%20polarised%20outcomes%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20reflects%20a%20disdain%20for%20basic%20constitutional%20morals%20and%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Fno-political-arena-should-look-like-a-football-stadium-11577896100534.html%5C%22%3ECAA-NRC-NPR%20combination%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowed%20for%20creating%20targets%20in%20a%20similar%20manner%2C%20and%20it%20went%20along%20with%20a%20state%20narrative%20to%20allow%20the%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20legitimatisation%E2%80%9D%20of%20a%20legalised%20political%20project%20of%20pitting%20one%20group%20in%20opposition%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20instance%20in%20this%20regard%20were%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fin-photos-remembering-the-farmers-protest-a-triumph-of-satyagraha-politics%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKaale%20Kanoon%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Black%20Farm%20Laws)%E2%80%9D%20brought%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20which%20divided%20farmers%2C%20and%20even%20those%20advocating%20for%20agri-reforms%2C%20leading%20