ki-Cuujm8Yad7A-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20full%20December%20data%20still%20outstanding%2C%202023%20has%20already%20qualified%20as%20the%20globe%E2%80%99s%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%20due%20to%20temperatures%20well%20above%20the%20average%20between%20June%20and%20November.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feu.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2024%2F01%2F01%2F2023-was-earths-hottest-year-experts-say%2F71882923007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSA%20Today%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20official%20hottest-year%20announcements%20from%20NASA%2C%20NOAA%20and%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20will%20follow%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%20For%20example%2C%20September%202023%20was%201.43%C2%B0%20C%20(2.57%C2%B0%20F)%20hotter%20than%20the%2020th%20century%20average%20temperature.%20Second-placed%20September%202020%20was%20just%200.98%C2%B0%20C%20(1.76%C2%B0%20F)%20hotter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncei.noaa.gov%2Faccess%2Fmonitoring%2Fclimate-at-a-glance%2Fglobal%2Ftime-series%2Fglobe%2Fland_ocean%2F1%2F1%2F1850-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20shows%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20the%20months%20of%20June%20through%20November%202023%20have%20been%20the%20hottest%20of%20their%20kinds%20since%20records%20started%20in%201850%20%E2%80%93%20with%20July%202023%20qualifying%20as%20the%20hottest%20of%20them%20all.%202023%20also%20saw%20the%20second-hottest%20March%20and%20the%20third-hottest%20May%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20years%20between%202014%20and%202023%20have%20been%20the%20ten%20warmest%20on%20record%20according%20to%20NASA%20and%20NOAA.%20The%20year%202016%2C%20which%20like%202023%20included%20the%20influence%20of%20a%20strong%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%2C%20was%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20Earth%20at%20its%20conclusion.%20It%20was%20about%20matched%20by%202020%20and%20both%20will%20now%20be%20overtaken%20by%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20fluctuating%20temperatures%20and%20very%20hot%2C%20very%20dry%20or%20very%20cold%20days%20are%20a%20normal%20phenomenon%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F5438%2Fweather-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20weather%20events%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20become%20more%20frequent%20and%20severe%20due%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F1148%2Fglobal-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Overall%2C%20a%20higher%20concentration%20of%20CO%E2%82%82%20and%20other%20climate%20gases%20in%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%20has%20led%20to%20rising%20average%20global%20temperatures%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.nasa.gov%2Fscientific-consensus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escientific%20consensus%20has%20found.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Expected%20to%20Be%20Hottest%20Year%20on%20Record%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F18267%2Faverage-global-temperature-records%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Expected%20to%20Be%20Hottest%20Year%20on%20Record%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.statcdn.com%2FInfographic%2Fimages%2Fnormal%2F18267.jpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EYou%20will%20find%20more%20infographics%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchartoftheday%2F%5C%22%3EStatista%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20this%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F18267%2Faverage-global-temperature-records%2F%3Futm_source%3DStatista%2BNewsletters%26utm_campaign%3D70e44e3955-COM_DailyData_Tue_%2BKW01_2024%26utm_medium%3Demai